For fairness to QAnswer, which specifically deals with count queries by aggregating on top of the SPARQL query, we queried the system\footnote{QAnswer API at \url{https://qanswer-core1.univ-st-etienne.fr/swagger-ui.html}} twice - the original count query (for the count answer) and a modified variant as in Section (ref), i.e., replacing ``how many'' with ``which''. We then
post-processed the results to extract count and instances.